{"word":"ἐπικλίνω","slug":"ἐπικλίνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπικλίνω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-κλῐνῶ</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to put</i> a door <i>to</i>: <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <el>ἐπικεκλῐμέναι σανίδες</el> <i>closed</i> doors, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to bend towards</i>, <el>τὰ ὦτα ἐπ.</el> <i>to prick</i> the ears, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:— <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>κεραῖαι ἐπικεκλιμέναι</el> spars <i>inclined at an angle to</i> the wall, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> <i>to incline towards</i>, <el>πρός τι</el> <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to lie over against</i> a place, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>IV. </b>in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, also, <i>to lie down at table</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}